job.description:
Accendero&amp;nbsp;Software, Inc. is seeking a candidate to fill the role of Software Engineer I at their Idaho Falls, ID location.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Accendero&amp;nbsp;Software, Inc. works with&amp;nbsp;state of the art&amp;nbsp;start-ups and companies to help build the next generation of scientific and operational software infrastructure.&amp;nbsp;   The ideal candidate is a passionate developer who has experience with all levels of the software development lifecycle.&amp;nbsp;This candidate should be prepared to immediately contribute in an agile engineering development and show leadership within a team of Junior Software Engineers.&amp;nbsp;The ideal candidate should be prepared to adapt to changing requirements and deadlines&amp;nbsp;in order to&amp;nbsp;best suit customer needs.   Accendero&amp;nbsp;Software, Inc.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;is an Equal&amp;nbsp;Opportunity&amp;nbsp;Employer and&amp;nbsp;provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability or genetics.&amp;nbsp;   Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;  - Develop new software applications for clients in multiple languages depending on client needs.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Integrate with currently existing software applications to expand functionality depending on client needs.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Coordinate with Project Management and senior Engineering to ensure all code is tested and prepared in a timely manner.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Coordinate with Project Management and Quality to meet regulatory requirements for projects requiring&amp;nbsp;GxP&amp;nbsp;validation.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Respond to changing scope and deadlines smoothly and efficiently.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Take leadership roles on projects as required by Project Management.   
   Requirements:&amp;nbsp;  - A 4-year&amp;nbsp;college degree&amp;nbsp;(BS) in Computer Science or equivalent&amp;nbsp;from a major accredited university and 1-2 years of full-stack software development experience&amp;nbsp;OR&amp;nbsp;3-5 years of related experience in software engineering&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with the Software Development Lifecycle and associated best practices.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Proven work experience with&amp;nbsp;Python,&amp;nbsp;Java, and Javascript.   
  - Proven work experience with relational database structures.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Proven work experience with non-relational database structures, especially MongoDB.   
  - Proven work experience with various version control software systems (Bitbucket, Git, etc.)   
  - Proven work experience with RESTful APIs.   
  - Demonstrable knowledge of best practices for testing code and proven work experience with various third party test suites (Selenium, Jest, etc.)   
  - Excellent&amp;nbsp;problem-solving&amp;nbsp;skills and attention to detail.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Excellent oral and written communication skills&amp;nbsp;   
   Pluses:&amp;nbsp;  - Experience with AWS.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience within a development environment interacting with regulatory schemas such as&amp;nbsp;GxP&amp;nbsp;or ISO.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with various other web or statistical languages (R, PERL, Java, etc.).&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with Test Driven Development (TDD).&amp;nbsp;
